title.narrative: B. Faso - Education Access and Quality Improvement Project (EAQIP)

description.narrative: The project development objective is to support the Government of Burkina Faso to: (a) increase access to preschool education in the two poorest regions, secondary education in the five poorest regions, and (b) improve teaching and learning.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Annual Budgeted Action Plan (ABAP) | Description :An ABAP for the following year has to be prepared by September30 of each year during the implementation of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Mid-term review | Description :A mid-term review will be undertaken not later than two (2) years afterEffectiveness of the Project. | Due Date :31-May-2017

Finance Agreement :Ministry of Basic Education (MENA) Support to Project Coordination Unit (PCU) | Description :The ministry ofbasic education provides support to the PCU in all activities pertaining to basic education, including: pre-school activities, thecurriculum reform; the construction of public and private lower secondary schools; and the reinforcement of entities in charge ofplanning and monitoring basic education activities. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Ministry of Social Affairs and National Solidarity (MASSN) support to the PCU | Description :MASSN providessupport to the PCU in the identification and the monitoring of students from poor households in the five (5) poorest regions. |Frequency :Yearly
